<subSubSection pageNumber="344" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="344">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="344">
Note: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cristata">Barleria cristata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, with the type designated by Brummitt &amp; Vollesen, was proposed as conserved type of the genus by Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="344">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 558. 1992). However, the proposal was eventually ruled unnecessary by the General Committee (see Barrie, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="344">l.c.</emphasis>
55: 795-796. 2006 for a review of the history of this and related proposals).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
